The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 New Delhi, May 10: Ghaziabad police have arrested a principal for allegedly beating up a five-year-old student severely on a suspicion of theft.           Friday, Rohit Singh returned home with injury marks on his face, neck and back. It is not clear what Subodh Kumar accused the Class I student of stealing. His father Hari Singh said: My child has been admitted to the school barely a week ago. He cant even speak properly. It took us time to understand what had happened.                  
	 London (PTI): An Indian-origin woman is facing a years jail term in Britain for getting her son admitted in a leading state school on a false address, a British paper has reported. Mranil Patel, 41, has said she put her mothers address as her own on her son Rhys Patels form by mistake.                   
	 Pathankot (PTI): An army jawan, who was reportedly involved in passing classified information over the Internet to Pakistani authorities, allegedly committed suicide on Sunday. Salim Pasha hanged himself from a water tank in a toilet.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): Departmental probes can proceed against employees even after their retirement if the service rules provide for it, the Supreme Court said while upholding an appeal filed by the Bengal government against a Calcutta High Court ruling.                                                                                                                           
